CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "No City Help - Apple St. residents on Monday said that the city turned a deaf ear to their pleas for "Go Slow" signs or other measures to insure safety in this area, which has been made into a one-way street by the sliding of loose earth from the Belmar Gardens' hillside above. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Landslide cordoned off by wooden fence, with stone wall on left and cars and houses on right, Apple Street, Homewood
